When pressed on Chicago’s large, lingering fiscal problems he is scornful, slaps your correspondent’s knee, then adds a sharp kick to his foot.
Mr Emanuel shrank the city’s structural deficit by hundreds of millions of dollars by cutting spending and increasing taxes.
Mr Emanuel prodded firms such as McDonald’s to bring their headquarters to Chicago.
Mr Emanuel claims the average child will gain the equivalent of an extra four years in school as a result.
If Mr Emanuel thinks everything has gone so well, why did he back out of his well-funded bid for a third term last September?